correctness.rationale: Extensive schema and factual issues. (1) Null/empty values violate the schema and the task requirement of no empty/null fields: plasmaPower=null; pressure.quantityValue.numericValue=null; thicknessControl.growthPerCycle.values[].value.numericValue=null; thicknessControl.numberofCycles.numericValue=null; nucleationPeriod.numericValue=null; dosingTime and purgeTime numericValue=null; flowRates numericValue=null; multiple materialProperties fields (refractiveIndex, absorptionCoefficient, resistivity, carrierDensity, uniformity.variation, conformality.aspectRatio, elementalConcentration.values.quantityValue.numericValue, roughness.value, filmDensity.value) are null; onOffRatio.numericValue=null. (2) Several properties are incorrect or not traceable to the article: temperature=350 °C corresponds to post-anneal (350 °C, 30 min in air), not deposition temperature; substrate set to “thermally grown SiO2/Si substrates,” but IGZO was deposited on an ALD GI (Al2O3 or HfOx) over TiN on p+ Si; coReactant=O3 is not mentioned; aldMethod=TALD is not explicitly stated; saturation=True not reported; supercycleDesign (sequence and counts) not reported; precursors listed as “Not Found” for In2O3/Ga2O3/ZnO are placeholders, not valid extracted values; bandGap=3.0 eV is not measured (text only notes >3 eV). (3) While some values match (filmThickness=10 nm; device metrics: μ_FE=18.3 cm2/V·s, V_TH=1.1 V, SS=67.8 mV/dec; deviceStructure description aligns with Fig. 1a), the large number of nulls/placeholders and multiple unsupported or incorrect entries render the extraction largely non-compliant and not traceable. Corrections needed: remove all null/placeholder values or supply grounded values; fix temperature to deposition value (or omit if unknown); correct substrate; remove unsubstantiated co-reactant and ALD method; omit supercycle/precursors unless reported; only include band gap if measured; ensure all required fields are populated with valid, QUDT-compliant values grounded in the text.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incomplete and contains factual and schema violations. Key issues: (1) Reactant details missing or incorrect: no precursors are reported (set as 'Not Found') and the co-reactant is asserted as O3 without support in the article; carrier/purging gases are 'Not Found'. (2) Process conditions are wrong or absent: deposition temperature is incorrectly taken as the anneal temperature (350 °C); reactor pressure is None; dosing/purge times and flow rates are None. (3) Thickness control is incomplete: growth-per-cycle and number of cycles are None; supercycle design lacks subcycle counts and the provided sequence is unsubstantiated by the text. (4) Multiple schema violations: many numeric fields contain null/None (pressure, GPC, cycles, dosing/purge times, flows, uniformity, conformality, composition, roughness, density, on/off ratio), and plasmaPower is set to None instead of a valid object—violating required data types and the schema’s non-null requirement. (5) Material properties are largely absent or speculative: band gap set to 3.0 eV is not measured for this film (only a general statement >3 eV appears); other optical/electrical properties are unset. (6) Device properties: only μFE, Vth, SS are correctly captured; on/off ratio is None. (7) Missing processes: the article describes ALD of IGZO as well as ALD of gate insulators (Al2O3/HfOx) and ALD SiO2 passivation and compares annealed vs. as-fabricated devices; only a single IGZO process instance is provided. Properties to add/review: verified precursors and co-reactant per sub-oxide, actual deposition temperature and pressure, dosing/purge/flow parameters, supercycle a:b:c counts, GPC and cycles, film composition/phase characterization methods, on/off ratio, and separate process instances for GI and passivation ALD if required by scope. Overall, the output is neither complete nor traceable and fails multiple schema constraints.
